## Limitations

The clandestine nature of money laundering means that much of the data is based on estimates and reported cases, which may not fully capture the scope of the issue. Additionally, the rapidly evolving techniques, especially with the advent of digital currencies, pose ongoing challenges to keeping information current. The reliance on publicly available sources may also limit access to the most recent and detailed law enforcement data.